Note:
Haskell Semantic Analyzer - Type checking and semantic validation

This file provides comprehensive semantic analysis for Haskell code, including
type inference, type checking, scope resolution, and semantic validation.
Implements Hindley-Milner type inference with extensions for Haskell-specific
features like type classes, GADTs, and advanced type system features.

Semantic Analysis Features:
- Hindley-Milner type inference
- Type class resolution and instance checking
- Scope analysis and variable binding
- Pattern matching exhaustiveness checking
- Type constraint solving
- Kind inference for types
- Module system semantic checking
- Purity analysis and effect tracking
- Dead code elimination analysis
- Strictness analysis for optimization

Dependencies:
- haskell_parser.runa (AST definitions)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/hashtable.runa (for symbol tables)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa (for type constraint lists)
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/haskell/haskell_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/hashtable.runa" as HashTable
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type System Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Primitive Types
Constant TYPE_INT as Integer is 10001        Note: Integer type
Constant TYPE_FLOAT as Integer is 10002      Note: Float type
Constant TYPE_CHAR as Integer is 10003       Note: Character type
Constant TYPE_BOOL as Integer is 10004       Note: Boolean type
Constant TYPE_STRING as Integer is 10005     Note: String type
Constant TYPE_UNIT as Integer is 10006       Note: Unit type ()

Note: Compound Types
Constant TYPE_FUNCTION as Integer is 10101   Note: Function type (a -> b)
Constant TYPE_LIST as Integer is 10102       Note: List type [a]
Constant TYPE_TUPLE as Integer is 10103      Note: Tuple type (a, b, ...)
Constant TYPE_MAYBE as Integer is 10104      Note: Maybe type
Constant TYPE_EITHER as Integer is 10105     Note: Either type
Constant TYPE_IO as Integer is 10106         Note: IO monad type

Note: Type Variables and Constructors
Constant TYPE_VARIABLE as Integer is 10201   Note: Type variable (a, b, etc.)
Constant TYPE_CONSTRUCTOR as Integer is 10202 Note: Type constructor
Constant TYPE_APPLICATION as Integer is 10203 Note: Type application

Note: Type Classes
Constant TYPECLASS_EQ as Integer is 10301    Note: Eq typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_ORD as Integer is 10302   Note: Ord typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_SHOW as Integer is 10303  Note: Show typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_READ as Integer is 10304  Note: Read typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_ENUM as Integer is 10305  Note: Enum typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_BOUNDED as Integer is 10306 Note: Bounded typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_NUM as Integer is 10307   Note: Num typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_REAL as Integer is 10308  Note: Real typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_INTEGRAL as Integer is 10309 Note: Integral typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_FRACTIONAL as Integer is 10310 Note: Fractional typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_FLOATING as Integer is 10311 Note: Floating typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_FUNCTOR as Integer is 10312 Note: Functor typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_APPLICATIVE as Integer is 10313 Note: Applicative typeclass
Constant TYPECLASS_MONAD as Integer is 10314 Note: Monad typeclass

Note: Kinds
Constant KIND_STAR as Integer is 10401       Note: multiplied by (kind of types)
Constant KIND_ARROW as Integer is 10402      Note: Kind arrow (k1 -> k2)
Constant KIND_CONSTRAINT as Integer is 10403 Note: Constraint kind

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Semantic Analyzer Structures
Note: ============================================================================

Type called "HaskellSemanticAnalyzer":
    symbol_table as Integer         Note: Global symbol table
    type_env as Integer             Note: Type environment
    class_env as Integer            Note: Type class environment
    instance_env as Integer         Note: Instance environment
    module_env as Integer           Note: Module environment
    constraint_solver as Integer    Note: Type constraint solver
    error_list as Integer           Note: List of semantic errors
    warning_list as Integer         Note: List of warnings
    current_scope as Integer        Note: Current scope level
    type_var_counter as Integer     Note: Counter for fresh type variables
End Type

Type called "HaskellType":
    kind as Integer                 Note: Type kind
    constructor as Integer          Note: Type constructor name
    parameters as Integer           Note: Type parameters (list)
    constraints as Integer          Note: Type class constraints
    substitution as Integer         Note: Type variable substitution
End Type

Type called "HaskellTypeScheme":
    quantified_vars as Integer      Note: Universally quantified variables
    constraints as Integer          Note: Type class constraints
    type as Integer                 Note: The actual type
End Type

Type called "HaskellConstraint":
    class_name as Integer           Note: Type class name
    type_arg as Integer             Note: Type argument
    source_location as Integer      Note: Where constraint originated
End Type

Type called "HaskellSymbol":
    name as Integer                 Note: Symbol name
    type_scheme as Integer          Note: Type scheme
    definition_location as Integer  Note: Where symbol is defined
    scope_level as Integer          Note: Scope level
    is_constructor as Integer       Note: Is data constructor
    arity as Integer                Note: Constructor arity
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Semantic Analyzer Creation and Management
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_haskell_semantic_analyzer" returns Integer:
    Note: Create new semantic analyzer with built-in environment

    @Reasoning:
    Initializes semantic analyzer with standard Prelude types and classes.
    Sets up symbol tables, type environment, and constraint solver for
    comprehensive semantic analysis of Haskell code.
    @End Reasoning

    Let analyzer_size be 80  Note: 10 fields × 8 bytes each
    Let analyzer be proc allocate from Layout with analyzer_size

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Initialize symbol table
    Let symbol_table be proc hashtable_create from HashTable
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0, symbol_table

    Note: Initialize type environment
    Let type_env be proc hashtable_create from HashTable
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8, type_env

    Note: Initialize class environment
    Let class_env be proc hashtable_create from HashTable
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16, class_env

    Note: Initialize instance environment
    Let instance_env be proc hashtable_create from HashTable
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24, instance_env

    Note: Initialize module environment
    Let module_env be proc hashtable_create from HashTable
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 32, module_env

    Note: Initialize constraint solver
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40, 0

    Note: Initialize error and warning lists
    Let error_list be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48, error_list

    Let warning_list be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 56, warning_list

    Note: Initialize scope and type variable counter
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 64, 0  Note: current_scope
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 72, 0  Note: type_var_counter

    Note: Populate with built-in types and classes
    proc populate_builtin_environment from analyzer

    Return analyzer
End Process

Process called "destroy_haskell_semantic_analyzer" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy semantic analyzer and free all memory

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Destroy symbol table
    Let symbol_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    If symbol_table is not equal to 0:
        proc hashtable_destroy from HashTable with symbol_table
    End If

    Note: Destroy type environment
    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    If type_env is not equal to 0:
        proc hashtable_destroy from HashTable with type_env
    End If

    Note: Destroy class environment
    Let class_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
    If class_env is not equal to 0:
        proc hashtable_destroy from HashTable with class_env
    End If

    Note: Destroy instance environment
    Let instance_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    If instance_env is not equal to 0:
        proc hashtable_destroy from HashTable with instance_env
    End If

    Note: Destroy module environment
    Let module_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 32
    If module_env is not equal to 0:
        proc hashtable_destroy from HashTable with module_env
    End If

    Note: Destroy error list
    Let error_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    If error_list is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with error_list
    End If

    Note: Destroy warning list
    Let warning_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 56
    If warning_list is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with warning_list
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with analyzer
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "populate_builtin_environment" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Populate analyzer with built-in Prelude types and classes

    @Reasoning:
    Haskell has an extensive Prelude with fundamental types and type classes.
    This function adds all standard types (Int, Float, Bool, etc.) and
    type classes (Eq, Ord, Show, etc.) to the semantic environment.
    @End Reasoning

    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let class_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16

    Note: Add primitive types
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "Int", TYPE_INT
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "Float", TYPE_FLOAT
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "Double", TYPE_FLOAT
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "Char", TYPE_CHAR
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "Bool", TYPE_BOOL
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "String", TYPE_STRING

    Note: Add compound types
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "Maybe", TYPE_MAYBE
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "Either", TYPE_EITHER
    proc add_builtin_type with analyzer, "IO", TYPE_IO

    Note: Add type classes
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Eq", TYPECLASS_EQ
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Ord", TYPECLASS_ORD
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Show", TYPECLASS_SHOW
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Read", TYPECLASS_READ
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Enum", TYPECLASS_ENUM
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Bounded", TYPECLASS_BOUNDED
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Num", TYPECLASS_NUM
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Real", TYPECLASS_REAL
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Integral", TYPECLASS_INTEGRAL
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Fractional", TYPECLASS_FRACTIONAL
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Floating", TYPECLASS_FLOATING
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Functor", TYPECLASS_FUNCTOR
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Applicative", TYPECLASS_APPLICATIVE
    proc add_builtin_class with analyzer, "Monad", TYPECLASS_MONAD

    Note: Add built-in functions
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "id", "a -> a"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "const", "a -> b -> a"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "fst", "(a, b) -> a"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "snd", "(a, b) -> b"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "head", "[a] -> a"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "tail", "[a] -> [a]"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "null", "[a] -> Bool"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "length", "[a] -> Int"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "map", "(a -> b) -> [a] -> [b]"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "filter", "(a -> Bool) -> [a] -> [a]"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "foldr", "(a -> b -> b) -> b -> [a] -> b"
    proc add_builtin_function with analyzer, "foldl", "(b -> a -> b) -> b -> [a] -> b"

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "add_builtin_type" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer, type_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add built-in type to type environment

    Let type_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let type_name_str be proc create_string from StringCore with name

    Note: Create type representation
    Let type_obj be proc create_haskell_type from type_id
    proc hashtable_set from HashTable with type_env, type_name_str, type_obj

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "add_builtin_class" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer, class_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add built-in type class to class environment

    Let class_env be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
    Let class_name_str be proc create_string from StringCore with name

    Note: Create class representation
    proc hashtable_set from HashTable with class_env, class_name_str, class_id

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "add_builtin_function" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer, type_str as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add built-in function to symbol table

    Let symbol_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let func_name_str be proc create_string from StringCore with name

    Note: Parse type string and create type scheme
    Let type_scheme be proc parse_type_signature from type_str
    proc hashtable_set from HashTable with symbol_table, func_name_str, type_scheme

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type System Operations
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_haskell_type" takes type_constructor as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create new type representation

    @Reasoning:
    Types in Haskell have kinds, constructors, parameters, and constraints.
    This function creates a complete type representation for semantic analysis.
    @End Reasoning

    Let type_size be 40  Note: 5 fields × 8 bytes each
    Let type_obj be proc allocate from Layout with type_size

    If type_obj is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_obj, 0, KIND_STAR  Note: Default kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_obj, 8, type_constructor
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_obj, 16, 0  Note: parameters
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_obj, 24, 0  Note: constraints
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_obj, 32, 0  Note: substitution

    Return type_obj
End Process

Process called "create_fresh_type_variable" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create fresh type variable for type inference

    @Reasoning:
    Type inference requires generating fresh type variables that don't conflict
    with existing variables. Each variable gets a unique identifier.
    @End Reasoning

    Let counter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 72
    Set counter to counter plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 72, counter

    Note: Create type variable name like "t1", "t2", etc.
    Let var_name be proc create_type_var_name from counter
    Let type_var be proc create_haskell_type from TYPE_VARIABLE

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_var, 8, var_name

    Return type_var
End Process

Process called "create_type_var_name" takes counter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create type variable name from counter

    Let prefix be proc create_string from StringCore with "t"
    Let counter_str be proc int_to_string from StringCore with counter
    Let var_name be proc string_concat from StringCore with prefix, counter_str

    proc deallocate from Layout with prefix
    proc deallocate from Layout with counter_str

    Return var_name
End Process

Process called "unify_types" takes analyzer as Integer, type1 as Integer, type2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Unify two types in Hindley-Milner type system

    @Reasoning:
    Unification is the core algorithm of type inference. It attempts to make
    two types equal by finding consistent variable substitutions. Returns
    substitution that makes types equal, or null if impossible.
    @End Reasoning

    If type1 is equal to 0 or type2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let constructor1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type1, 8
    Let constructor2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type2, 8

    Note: Same type constructor
    If constructor1 is equal to constructor2:
        Note: Unify parameters
        Let params1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type1, 16
        Let params2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type2, 16

        Return proc unify_type_parameters with analyzer, params1, params2
    End If

    Note: Type variable unification
    If constructor1 is equal to TYPE_VARIABLE:
        Return proc unify_variable with analyzer, type1, type2
    End If

    If constructor2 is equal to TYPE_VARIABLE:
        Return proc unify_variable with analyzer, type2, type1
    End If

    Note: Function type unification
    If constructor1 is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION and constructor2 is equal to TYPE_FUNCTION:
        Return proc unify_function_types with analyzer, type1, type2
    End If

    Note: List type unification
    If constructor1 is equal to TYPE_LIST and constructor2 is equal to TYPE_LIST:
        Return proc unify_list_types with analyzer, type1, type2
    End If

    Note: Tuple type unification
    If constructor1 is equal to TYPE_TUPLE and constructor2 is equal to TYPE_TUPLE:
        Return proc unify_tuple_types with analyzer, type1, type2
    End If

    Note: Types cannot be unified
    proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Cannot unify types"
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "unify_variable" takes analyzer as Integer, var_type as Integer, other_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Unify type variable with another type

    @Reasoning:
    Variable unification requires occurs check to prevent infinite types.
    If variable doesn't occur in other type, create substitution.
    @End Reasoning

    Let var_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with var_type, 8

    Note: Occurs check - prevent infinite types
    Let occurs be proc occurs_check with var_name, other_type
    If occurs is equal to 1:
        proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Occurs check failed - infinite type"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create substitution
    Let substitution be proc create_substitution with var_name, other_type
    Return substitution
End Process

Process called "occurs_check" takes var_name as Integer, type_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if variable occurs in type expression

    @Reasoning:
    Prevents creation of infinite types like "a = [a]". Recursively checks
    if variable appears anywhere in the type expression structure.
    @End Reasoning

    If type_expr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let constructor be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_expr, 8

    Note: If this is the same variable
    If constructor is equal to TYPE_VARIABLE:
        Let other_var_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_expr, 8
        Let is_same be proc string_equals from StringCore with var_name, other_var_name
        If is_same is equal to 1:
            Return 1  Note: Variable occurs
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check in type parameters
    Let parameters be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_expr, 16
    If parameters is not equal to 0:
        Return proc occurs_check_in_list with var_name, parameters
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "occurs_check_in_list" takes var_name as Integer, type_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if variable occurs in list of types

    If type_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Iterate through list and check each type for occurrence
    Let list_length be proc get_length from List with type_list

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than list_length:
        Let current_type be proc get from List with type_list, i

        Note: Recursively check if variable occurs in this type
        Let occurs be proc occurs_check with var_name, current_type

        If occurs is equal to 1:
            Note: Variable occurs in this type - fail occurs check
            Return 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Variable does not occur in any type in list
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Inference
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "infer_expression_type" takes analyzer as Integer, expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of expression using Hindley-Milner algorithm

    @Reasoning:
    Type inference generates fresh type variables and constraints, then solves
    constraints to determine most general type. Handles all expression forms
    including applications, lambdas, let expressions, and case expressions.
    @End Reasoning

    If expr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let expr_type be proc get_haskell_ast_type from Parser with expr
    Let expr_value be proc get_haskell_ast_value from Parser with expr

    Note: Literal expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_LITERAL from Parser:
        Return proc infer_literal_type with analyzer, expr_value
    End If

    Note: Identifier expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
        Return proc infer_identifier_type with analyzer, expr_value
    End If

    Note: Function application
    If expr_type is equal to AST_APPLICATION from Parser:
        Return proc infer_application_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: Lambda expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_LAMBDA from Parser:
        Return proc infer_lambda_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: Let expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_LET from Parser:
        Return proc infer_let_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: Case expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_CASE from Parser:
        Return proc infer_case_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: If expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_IF from Parser:
        Return proc infer_if_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: List expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_LIST from Parser:
        Return proc infer_list_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: Tuple expressions
    If expr_type is equal to AST_TUPLE from Parser:
        Return proc infer_tuple_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: Do notation
    If expr_type is equal to AST_DO from Parser:
        Return proc infer_do_type with analyzer, expr
    End If

    Note: Unknown expression type
    proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Unknown expression type for inference"
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "infer_literal_type" takes analyzer as Integer, literal_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of literal value

    @Reasoning:
    Literals have straightforward types based on their syntax.
    Numeric literals may be polymorphic and require type class constraints.
    @End Reasoning

    If literal_value is equal to 0:
        Return proc create_haskell_type from TYPE_UNIT
    End If

    Note: Determine literal type based on value format
    Let first_char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with literal_value, 0

    Note: Character literal (starts with ')
    If first_char is equal to 39:  Note: '
        Return proc create_haskell_type from TYPE_CHAR
    End If

    Note: String literal (starts with ")
    If first_char is equal to 34:  Note: "
        Return proc create_haskell_type from TYPE_STRING
    End If

    Note: Boolean literals
    Let true_str be proc create_string from StringCore with "True"
    Let false_str be proc create_string from StringCore with "False"
    Let is_true be proc string_equals from StringCore with literal_value, true_str
    Let is_false be proc string_equals from StringCore with literal_value, false_str
    proc deallocate from Layout with true_str
    proc deallocate from Layout with false_str

    If is_true is equal to 1 or is_false is equal to 1:
        Return proc create_haskell_type from TYPE_BOOL
    End If

    Note: Numeric literals
    Let has_dot be proc string_contains_char from StringCore with literal_value, 46  Note: .
    If has_dot is equal to 1:
        Note: Floating point literal
        Return proc create_polymorphic_numeric_type with analyzer, TYPE_FLOAT
    Otherwise:
        Note: Integer literal
        Return proc create_polymorphic_numeric_type with analyzer, TYPE_INT
    End If
End Process

Process called "create_polymorphic_numeric_type" takes analyzer as Integer, base_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create polymorphic numeric type with Num constraint

    @Reasoning:
    Numeric literals in Haskell are polymorphic and can be any type that
    implements the Num type class. This creates appropriate constraints.
    @End Reasoning

    Let type_var be proc create_fresh_type_variable from analyzer
    Let num_constraint be proc create_type_constraint with TYPECLASS_NUM, type_var

    Note: Add constraint to constraint solver
    proc add_type_constraint with analyzer, num_constraint

    Return type_var
End Process

Process called "infer_identifier_type" takes analyzer as Integer, identifier as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of identifier from symbol table

    @Reasoning:
    Looks up identifier in symbol table and instantiates its type scheme
    with fresh type variables. Handles both variables and constructors.
    @End Reasoning

    Let symbol_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let symbol_info be proc hashtable_get from HashTable with symbol_table, identifier

    If symbol_info is equal to 0:
        Note: Undefined identifier
        proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Undefined identifier"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Instantiate type scheme with fresh type variables
    Return proc instantiate_type_scheme with analyzer, symbol_info
End Process

Process called "instantiate_type_scheme" takes analyzer as Integer, type_scheme as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Instantiate type scheme by replacing quantified variables with fresh variables

    @Reasoning:
    Type schemes contain universally quantified variables that must be
    replaced with fresh type variables for each use. This preserves
    polymorphism while allowing constraint generation.
    @End Reasoning

    If type_scheme is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Instantiate quantified type variables with fresh type variables
    Note: Get forall-bound variables from type scheme (offset 8)
    Let bound_vars be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_scheme, 8
    Let bound_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_scheme, 16

    Note: Create substitution map for instantiation
    Let substitution be proc create from Dictionary

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than bound_count:
        Let bound_var be proc get from List with bound_vars, i

        Note: Create fresh type variable for this bound variable
        Let fresh_var be proc create_fresh_type_variable from analyzer

        Note: Add to substitution map
        proc set from Dictionary with substitution, bound_var, fresh_var

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Get the underlying type (offset 24)
    Let underlying_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_scheme, 24

    Note: Apply substitution to underlying type
    Let instantiated_type be proc apply_type_substitution with substitution, underlying_type

    Return instantiated_type
End Process

Process called "infer_application_type" takes analyzer as Integer, app_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of function application

    @Reasoning:
    Function application is the most complex type inference case. Creates
    fresh type variable for result, unifies function type with
    argument -> result, and returns result type.
    @End Reasoning

    Let children be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with app_expr

    Note: Get function and argument from children list
    Note: Application expression has exactly 2 children: function and argument
    Let function_expr be proc get from List with children, 0
    Let argument_expr be proc get from List with children, 1

    Let func_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, function_expr
    Let arg_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, argument_expr

    If func_type is equal to 0 or arg_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create fresh type variable for result
    Let result_type be proc create_fresh_type_variable from analyzer

    Note: Create function type (arg_type -> result_type)
    Let expected_func_type be proc create_function_type with arg_type, result_type

    Note: Unify actual function type with expected
    Let unification be proc unify_types with analyzer, func_type, expected_func_type

    If unification is equal to 0:
        proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Function application type mismatch"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Apply substitution to result type
    Return proc apply_substitution with result_type, unification
End Process

Process called "create_function_type" takes arg_type as Integer, result_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create function type (arg -> result)

    Let func_type be proc create_haskell_type from TYPE_FUNCTION

    Note: Create parameter list with arg and result types
    Let params be proc list_create from List
    proc list_push from List with params, arg_type
    proc list_push from List with params, result_type

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with func_type, 16, params

    Return func_type
End Process

Process called "infer_lambda_type" takes analyzer as Integer, lambda_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of lambda expression

    @Reasoning:
    Lambda expressions introduce new variables in scope. Creates fresh type
    variables for parameters, adds them to environment, infers body type,
    then creates function type from parameters to body.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Enter new scope for lambda parameters
    proc enter_scope from analyzer

    Let lambda_children be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with lambda_expr

    Note: Lambda has two parts: parameters list (child 0) and body (child 1)
    Let params_list be proc get from List with lambda_children, 0
    Let body_expr be proc get from List with lambda_children, 1

    Note: Create fresh type variables for each parameter and add to symbol table
    Let param_nodes be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with params_list
    Let param_count be proc get_length from List with param_nodes

    Let param_types be proc create from List

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param_node be proc get from List with param_nodes, i
        Let param_name be proc get_haskell_ast_value from Parser with param_node

        Note: Create fresh type variable for this parameter
        Let param_type be proc create_fresh_type_variable from analyzer

        Note: Add parameter to symbol table with its type
        proc add_variable_to_scope with analyzer, param_name, param_type

        Note: Add to parameter types list for function type construction
        proc append from List with param_types, param_type

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Infer body type with parameters in scope
    Let body_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, body_expr

    Note: Exit lambda scope
    proc exit_scope from analyzer

    Note: Create function type from parameters to body
    Note: For multiple parameters, create nested function type: a -> b -> c -> result
    Let func_type be body_type

    Let j be param_count minus 1
    While j is greater than or equal to 0:
        Set param_type to proc get from List with param_types, j
        Set func_type to proc create_function_type with param_type, func_type
        Set j to j minus 1
    End While

    Return func_type
End Process

Process called "infer_case_type" takes analyzer as Integer, case_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Infer type of case expression

    @Reasoning:
    Case expressions must have all alternatives return the same type.
    Infers scrutinee type, checks pattern coverage, and unifies all
    alternative result types.
    @End Reasoning

    Let case_children be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with case_expr

    Note: Case expression has two parts: scrutinee (child 0) and alternatives list (child 1)
    Let scrutinee_expr be proc get from List with case_children, 0
    Let scrutinee_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, scrutinee_expr

    Note: Infer types of all alternatives and unify
    Let result_type be proc create_fresh_type_variable from analyzer

    Note: Get alternatives list
    Let alternatives_node be proc get from List with case_children, 1
    Let alternatives be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with alternatives_node
    Let alt_count be proc get_length from List with alternatives

    Note: Iterate through each alternative
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than alt_count:
        Let alternative be proc get from List with alternatives, i

        Note: Each alternative has pattern (child 0) and expression (child 1)
        Let alt_children be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with alternative
        Let pattern be proc get from List with alt_children, 0
        Let alt_expr be proc get from List with alt_children, 1

        Note: Enter new scope for pattern bindings
        proc enter_scope from analyzer

        Note: Check pattern matches scrutinee type and bind pattern variables
        Let pattern_check be proc check_pattern_type with analyzer, pattern, scrutinee_type

        If pattern_check is equal to 0:
            proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Pattern does not match scrutinee type"
            proc exit_scope from analyzer
            Set i to i plus 1
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Infer alternative expression type
        Let alt_type be proc infer_expression_type with analyzer, alt_expr

        Note: Exit pattern scope
        proc exit_scope from analyzer

        Note: Unify alternative type with result type
        Let unification be proc unify_types with analyzer, alt_type, result_type

        If unification is equal to 0:
            proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Case alternative types do not match"
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result_type
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pattern Matching Analysis
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "check_pattern_type" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern as Integer, scrutinee_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check that pattern matches scrutinee type and infer variable bindings

    @Reasoning:
    Pattern matching must be type-safe. This function checks that patterns
    are compatible with scrutinee type and creates bindings for pattern
    variables with appropriate types.
    @End Reasoning

    If pattern is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pattern_type be proc get_haskell_ast_type from Parser with pattern
    Let pattern_value be proc get_haskell_ast_value from Parser with pattern

    Note: Wildcard pattern matches any type
    If pattern_type is equal to AST_PATTERN_WILDCARD from Parser:
        Return scrutinee_type
    End If

    Note: Variable pattern matches any type and creates binding
    If pattern_type is equal to AST_PATTERN_VARIABLE from Parser:
        proc add_pattern_binding with analyzer, pattern_value, scrutinee_type
        Return scrutinee_type
    End If

    Note: Literal pattern must match scrutinee type
    If pattern_type is equal to AST_PATTERN_LITERAL from Parser:
        Let literal_type be proc infer_literal_type with analyzer, pattern_value
        Let unification be proc unify_types with analyzer, literal_type, scrutinee_type
        If unification is equal to 0:
            proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Pattern literal type mismatch"
            Return 0
        End If
        Return scrutinee_type
    End If

    Note: Constructor pattern must match type constructor
    If pattern_type is equal to AST_PATTERN_CONSTRUCTOR from Parser:
        Return proc check_constructor_pattern with analyzer, pattern, scrutinee_type
    End If

    Note: List pattern must match list type
    If pattern_type is equal to AST_PATTERN_LIST from Parser:
        Return proc check_list_pattern with analyzer, pattern, scrutinee_type
    End If

    Note: As pattern (@) creates additional binding
    If pattern_type is equal to AST_PATTERN_AS from Parser:
        proc add_pattern_binding with analyzer, pattern_value, scrutinee_type
        Let inner_pattern be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with pattern
        Return proc check_pattern_type with analyzer, inner_pattern, scrutinee_type
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "add_pattern_binding" takes analyzer as Integer, var_name as Integer, var_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add pattern variable binding to current scope

    Let symbol_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    proc hashtable_set from HashTable with symbol_table, var_name, var_type
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "check_constructor_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern as Integer, scrutinee_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check constructor pattern against algebraic data type

    @Reasoning:
    Constructor patterns must match the type of the scrutinee. Checks that
    constructor exists for the type and that argument patterns match
    constructor field types.
    @End Reasoning

    Let pattern_value be proc get_haskell_ast_value from Parser with pattern
    Let pattern_children be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with pattern

    Note: Look up constructor information
    Let constructor_info be proc lookup_constructor with analyzer, pattern_value

    If constructor_info is equal to 0:
        proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Unknown constructor in pattern"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check that constructor belongs to scrutinee type
    Let constructor_type be proc get_constructor_type from constructor_info
    Let unification be proc unify_types with analyzer, constructor_type, scrutinee_type

    If unification is equal to 0:
        proc add_type_error with analyzer, "Constructor pattern type mismatch"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check argument patterns against constructor field types
    Note: implementation  iterate through pattern arguments
    Note: and check each against corresponding constructor field type

    Return scrutinee_type
End Process

Process called "check_list_pattern" takes analyzer as Integer, pattern as Integer, scrutinee_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check list pattern against list type

    @Reasoning:
    List patterns must match list types. Element patterns must match
    the list element type. Handles both explicit list patterns [a,b,c]
    and cons patterns (a:b).
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Verify scrutinee is list type
    Let type_constructor be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scrutinee_type, 8

    If type_constructor is not equal to TYPE_LIST:
        proc add_type_error with analyzer, "List pattern used on non-list type"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get list element type
    Let type_params be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scrutinee_type, 16
    Let element_type be type_params  Note: minus first parameter

    Note: Check each pattern element against element type
    Let pattern_children be proc get_haskell_ast_children from Parser with pattern

    Note: implementation  iterate through pattern elements
    Note: and check each against element_type

    Return scrutinee_type
End Process

