Process called "enter_scope" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Enter new lexical scope

    Let current_scope be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 64
    Set current_scope to current_scope plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 64, current_scope

    Return current_scope
End Process

Process called "exit_scope" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Exit current lexical scope and remove local bindings

    Let current_scope be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 64

    If current_scope is greater than 0:
        Note: Remove symbols from current scope level
        proc remove_scope_symbols with analyzer, current_scope

        Set current_scope to current_scope minus 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 64, current_scope
    End If

    Return current_scope
End Process

Process called "remove_scope_symbols" takes analyzer as Integer, scope_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Remove all symbols from specified scope level

    Let symbol_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0

    Note: implementation  iterate through symbol table
    Note: and remove all symbols with matching scope level

    Return 1
End Process

